==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: made-to-order
<hw>made-to-order</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>made specially
for a specific purpose; -- of articles of manufacture. Contrasted with
<er>mass-produced</er>, <er>standard</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> custom-made.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>made or tailored to fit a specific person; -- of
clothing. Contrasted with <er>off-the-rack</er>,
<er>ready-to-wear</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> custom-made, custom-tailored.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>made-up</ent>⟦br⟧
